box": [54.8, 400.4, 723.6, 410.5]}, {"text": "Group work 22.3 41.7 36.1 29.3", "bbox": [54.8, 416.2, 723.6, 426.3]}, {"text": "Aspect of student learning assessed", "bbox": [45.5, 431.9, 187.3, 442.0]}, {"text": "Knowledge 91.1 97.8 72.8 88.1", "bbox": [54.8, 447.8, 723.6, 457.9]}, {"text": "Attitudes 58.3 57.7 61.5 70.9", "bbox": [54.8, 463.5, 723.6, 473.6]}, {"text": "Practical/life skills 48.4 53.3 36.1 34.3", "bbox": [54.8, 479.3, 723.6, 489.4]}, {"text": "ACCORDING TO STUDENTS (all schools) (N = 2,484) (N = 2,990) (N = 2,528) (N = 3,004)", "bbox": [45.5, 495.0, 697.9, 505.2]}, {"text": "Are CSE topics included in exams? 76.0 98.7 57.1 44.4", "bbox": [54.8, 510.9, 723.6, 521.0]}, {"text": "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0200513.t003", "bbox": [45.5, 529.2, 236.2, 539.8]}, {"text": "subject components. As such, no specific and consistent monitoring of CSE is being conducted", "bbox": [252.5, 559.0, 727.2, 571.6]}, {"text": "in these countries:", "bbox": [252.5, 575.4, 343.9, 588.1]}, {"text": "We are not monitoring as much as we should. So we cannot vouch for every school, every", "bbox": [267.6, 607.0, 716.2, 619.6]}, {"text": "teacher that they are actually teaching all the issues about adolescent reproductive health.", "bbox": [267.6, 623.4, 712.5, 636.0]}, {"text": "So that is another challenge. The feedback mechanism for us to know how much is being", "bbox": [267.6, 639.8, 712.2, 652.4]}, {"text": "taught is not adequate. [MoE official, Accra, Ghana]", "bbox": [267.6, 656.2, 528.9, 668.8]}, {"text": "The CSE workshops offered in schools by the health sector, with support from international", "bbox": [267.6, 687.7, 726.9, 700.4]}, {"text": "agencies, are more closely evaluated, but even this evaluation consists more in confirming that", "bbox": [252.5, 704.2, 724.1, 716.8]}, {"text": "the workshops happened than in collecting any meaningful impact measures. Key informants", "bbox": [252.5, 720.6, 721.0, 733.2]}, {"text": "in Kenya and Ghana also noted the lack of impact evaluations to determine the effect of CSE", "bbox": [252.5, 737.0, 714.7, 749.6]}, {"text": "on student outcomes. One Peruvian informant emphasized the key role of such evaluations in", "bbox": [252.5, 753.4, 722.5, 766.1]}, {"text": "program success:", "bbox": [252.5, 769.8, 338.5, 782.5]}, {"text": "Interviewer: And from the political level, how do you think CSE could be given more", "bbox": [267.6, 801.4, 692.8, 814.0]}, {"text": "support?", "bbox": [267.6, 817.8, 311.4, 830.4]}, {"text": "Respondent: First, it would have to be budgeted. It would need to be regulated. And most", "bbox": [267.6, 841.8, 714.5, 854.4]}, {"text": "of all, include a budget for monitoring and follow-up. And there should be an evaluation:", "bbox": [267.6, 858.2, 713.7, 870.9]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0200513 July 11, 2018 12 / 18", "bbox": [45.5, 946.7, 727.3, 956.8]}]}